column2: No information whatsoever can be inferred from this exceptional value (e.g., unknown if systemic therapy was administered).
No proper value is applicable in this context (e.g., no systemic therapy was administered; autopsy only case).
A proper value is applicable but not known. This event occurred, but the date is unknown (e.g., systemic therapy administered but date is unknown).

Information is not available at this time, but it is expected that it will be available later (e.g., systemic therapy is planned as part of the first course of therapy, but had not been started at the time of the most recent follow-up).
A valid date value is provided in item RX Date Systemic [3230], or the date was not expected to have been transmitted.
